Good question! Wix doesn't allow you to place static files in your web root, so you'll need to use a **proxy approach** instead [1].

Here's how to set it up:

## Proxy via Cloudflare Workers (Recommended)

1. **Get your slug** from the Setup tab — it appears in the proxy URLs shown there (e.g., `example-wixsite-com`)

2. **Set up a Cloudflare Worker** to proxy requests:
   - Go to Cloudflare → Workers & Pages → Create application
   - Create a new worker with this code:
     ```javascript
     export default {
       async fetch(request) {
         const url = new URL(request.url);
         if (url.pathname === '/llms.txt' || url.pathname === '/llms-full.txt') {
           const slug = 'example-wixsite-com'; // Your slug from Setup tab
           const proxyUrl = `https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/${slug}${url.pathname}`;
           return fetch(proxyUrl);
         }
         return fetch(request); // Pass through other requests to Wix
       }
     }
     ```
   - Deploy and connect to your domain

3. **Verify** that `https://yourdomain.com/llms.txt` now returns your GEO file

Your llms.txt will now automatically update whenever you re-run audits in GEO — no manual redeployment needed.

